headline: Will DIY stocks continue to be challenged? Citi weighs in
summary: Investing.com -- Citi analysts say the do-it-yourself (DIY) segment continues to show signs of weakness in the second quarter, with both Home Depot (NYSE:HD) and Lowe’s (NYSE:LOW) experiencing soft traffic trends and relying increasingly on Pro customer strength to offset declines.
